Distribution Type,Description,Example,Use Case
Hash Distribution,"Data is distributed based on the hash value of a key column.","Orders are distributed by CustomerID, ensuring rows with the same customer go to the same node.","Evenly spreads data and is efficient for joins on the distribution key."
Round-Robin Distribution,"Rows are distributed evenly but without any specific order or pattern.",N/A,"Simple to implement but less efficient for joins."
Replicated Distribution,"The table is fully replicated across all nodes.",N/A,"Small tables that are frequently used in joins benefit from replication for faster access."
